Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450}(lengthways into 1cm slices), then chop
into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel). Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle
with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway
through. Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60}.

Put the @panko breadcrumbs{10} and @water{2} into a large #bowl{}, then mix to combine.
Add the @British beef mince{240}. Season with the @salt{1/4} and @pepper{} then mix
together with your hands. Roll the mince into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick
burgers (1 per person).

> The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Lay in the
@British streaky bacon{4} rashers and fry until crispy and brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on each
side. Transfer to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.
> Do not discard the fat.

Pop the bacon frying pan back on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the burgers and fry
until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-14%minutes} in total. Carefully turn
them every ~{3-4%minutes} and lower the heat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the burgers are cooked, remove the pan from the heat. Carefully place the cheese
on top of the burgers. Cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}) then set aside, off the heat,
for ~{3-4%minutes} for the cheese to melt.

Meanwhile, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}. Reserve 1 leaf per burger, then halve the rest
lengthways and thinly slice widthways. Chop half the @medium tomato{2} into slices and
the rest into 1cm pieces. Halve the @glazed burger bun{2}. Pop onto a baking tray and
into your oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Just before serving, pop the
@French dressing{30} into a medium bowl with the baby gem and chopped tomatoes. Toss
together.

When everything is ready, divide the burger buns between your plates. Spread the
@burger sauce{135} onto the base of each bun. Add a baby gem leaf, then a burger patty,
and finish with the bacon and slice of tomato. Sandwich together, and serve up your
ultimate bacon cheeseburger with the chips and salad alongside. Enjoy!